         <abstract>
            <p>Professor W. Scott Bauman, in a recent Journal article, implied that those skeptical about earnings forecasts over 10 or more years, argue "against the scientific approach" to investment analysis. However, when these analysts base their stock appraisals consistently on certain concepts of postulated investment returns, they are at least as "scientific" as others who attempt to work with earnings projections reaching out over several decades. Whether appraisals are presented as present worth of future money rewards, or in sets of p/e multiples tied into appropriate postulated investment returns, is immaterial.</p>
          </abstract>
